commit.message: Fix NPE in CouchbaseCluster enricher
Fix riak (configureInternalNetwork throwing NPE)
Fix NPE generating Nginx config when no SSL configured

Avoid NullPointerException when removing primary from a replica set

getPrimary() checks all members but the entity that /was/ the primary
has been removed from the group by the time this log statement is reached.
If the set hasn't chosen a new primary and the sensors haven't updated
this causes a NullPointerException.

Merge pull request #1111 from grkvlt/fix/cassandra-npe

Fix NPE when CASSANDRA_CLUSTER_NODES not set
Avoid NPE in MongoDBShardClusterImpl
Added npe check

This closes #59

* github/pr/59:
  Fix NPE generating Nginx config when no SSL configured
Prevent DynamicCluster NPE when subclasses have not called super.init()
Avoid NPE in TomcatServer.disconnectSensors
Fix NPE in AbstractController.update
Fix NPE on getJmxSensors

Closes #69

Update default Zookeeper version and fix NPE

This updates the Zookeeper version to use (version 3.4.5 not available anymore).
It also fixes a NPE on customize phase, caused by:
- the `ZookeeperNode.MY_ID` not set for a single `ZookeeperNode`
- getZookeeperServers() expecting the parent to be and entity of type `ZookeeperEnsemble`, which is not the case for a single `ZookeeperNode`
Fix NPE in CassandraClusterImpl update of HostAndPort
avoid NPE when stopping after error (cassandra)
Fix NPE in TomcatServer.disconnectSensors (when inactive)
Eliminating NPE when port in use

Merge pull request #1344 from ahgittin/mongo

Mongo NPE check
Fix NPE when CASSANDRA_CLUSTER_NODES not set
Update default Zookeeper version and fix NPE on customize phase, caused by the ZookeeperNode.MY_ID and getZookeeperServers() when used to deploy only one node
tidy code for gathering couchbase sensors, and prevent NPE's using new functional methods
tidy of MongoDB client NPE check (as per discussion in #1327), and clearing isRunning on stop
Merge branch 'npe' of https://github.com/dave-finnegan/brooklyn into misc
Fix NPE in tests by adding instanceof check for cluster members
Review changes for #810 including fix for NPE and adding new reverse lookup attributes
create specs from catalog items, and use these in many places.  also fix some NPE and serialization issues.

Deletes keys defined in ConfigKeys

- Update all uses to the new BrooklynConfigKeys
- Was previously deprecated, with fields in ConfigKeys referencing
  those in BrooklynConfigKeys. But this led to strange NPEs where
  ConfigKeys fields were null (presumably due to ordering of
  initialising the two classes' fields)!
- Breaks backwards compatibility, but better to have a compilation error
  than a weird NPE.

Fix sharded-mongodb, with CoLocatedMongoDbRouter

- was getting NPE in CoLocatedMongoDbRouter.init, while trying to
  resolve config set in yam that pointed at another entity.

Merge pull request #1474 from ahgittin/couchbase

Couchbase code tidy, nicer way to define sensors, and prevent NPE's, using new `Functionals`

Improvements for PR #66

* Avoid NPE in in AbstractController.computePortsAndUrls() if inferUrl
  returns null.
* Remove some duplication from inferUrl*()
* Renames inferUrlPublic() to inferUrlForPublic() - and same for subnet
* testMainUriSensorsCorrectlyComputedWithoutDomain to use machineLocation
  extending HasSubnetHostname, so subnet address set as expected.
* Tidy deprecated code and generics in test.
fix misc errors during hot standby (access to unavailable methods, clearing more things on location unmanagement) and after rebind (NPE in SshMachineLocation), and fix sensor logic bug in tomcat

Fix integration tests

- NginxUrlMapping: test webapp changed, so writes out original url rather
  than url-mapping id
- Fix ElasticJavaWebAppServiceIntegrationTest
- Avoid NPE in ReflectionScanner if class can't be found
- fix RabbitSshDriver imports

Cleanup AbstractGeoDnsService.addTargetHost

- avoid NPE when hostname==null and ip!=null, and !USE_HOSTNAMES
- improve logging, so if log about hostname missing and then subsequent
  can't infer geo, then still log about the latter.
- general code cleanup; but more could be done.

Supports periodic persist for RebindManager

- Avoids hammering the CPU too much, by continually serializing
  mementos and persisting them.
- Fixes NPE in AbstractEntity.invalidate
- Fixes location rebind, where was overwriting all fields
  with their default values!
- In EntityManagementSupport, sets currentlyDeployed before
  calling onManagementStarting.
- ScheduledTask: make it useable from java
- Fixes SoftwareProcessEntity rebind (so provisioningLocation is
  restored, and stop can subsequently release the machine)
